The paper deals with multi-person pose estimation from 2D images, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new model architecture that utilizes multi-scale information, which is a common technique in deep learning and machine learning. This suggests that the paper could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses R-CNN, which is a popular object detection framework, indicating that it could also be classified under cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.RO (Robotics).
